BLOCK B — Cyber Threat Intelligence Lifecycle

Goal: Learn how threat intelligence is created and used from start to finish.

Time: 30–40 minutes


---

What is the CTI Lifecycle?

Threat intelligence is not just collecting threat reports.

It follows a structured cycle:

Requirements
      ↓
Collection
      ↓
Processing
      ↓
Analysis
      ↓
Dissemination
      ↓
Feedback
      ↺

Think of it like software development:

Requirement
↓

Coding

↓

Testing

↓

Deployment

↓

Feedback

↓

Next version

CTI works the same way.


---

Step 1 — Requirements

This answers:

> What do we want to know?



Security teams don't collect everything.

They define intelligence requirements.

Examples:

Are ransomware groups targeting banks?

Are attackers exploiting Bedrock?

Is prompt injection increasing?

Are our vendors compromised?

Is there any threat to Barclays infrastructure?


Without requirements, intelligence teams waste time collecting irrelevant data.


---

